<!DOCTYPE html>
<!--Piper's page-->
<html>
    <head>
        <!--The <head> element is a container for metadata and is placed between the <html> tag and the <body> tag-->
            <title>A SAMPLE HTML PAGE OF PIPER </title>
            <!--The <style> element is used to define style information for a single HTML page-->
            <style>
                h1 {color:pink;}
            </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>PIPER's PAGE</h1>
        <h2>I.About Me: </h2>
        <p> My name is Piper </p>
        <style>
            .myDiv {
            border: 1px outset black;
            background-color: FloralWhite;
            text-align: center;
        }
        </style>
        <!--A <div> section in a document that is styled with CSS:-->
        <div class="myDiv">
            <p> I am a senior Applied Computing student at UW Bothell.
            My goal is becoming an UX designer or UX researcher with Computer Science background.
            I love connecting other people in the UX design industry and use my ability to contribute our society. </p>
        </div>
        <h2>II.My Buddy:</h2>
        <!--A <span element which is used to color a part of a text-->
        <p> I have a cute little friend at home. His name is <span style="color: palevioletred"> <b>Peanut</b></span> "</p>
    </body>
</html>
